values:
well this last week has been pretty crazy because of all the fires... on monday the company i work for sent down a strike team of 4 ambulances to help evacuate hospitals and con homes in san diego and i worked overtime trying to get supplies together for our strike team and keeping all the kous undercontrol to some extent at least... i left work on monday stressed and overworked and i went to meet beth at the VFW that we hang out at sometimes, when i get there she has been drinking so i dont feel i can talk to her about my day although she isnt drunk or anything....and this leaves me feeling like she isnt fulfilling her duties of being supportive and she doesnt think im filling mine either, she is upset because she came to the realization that i do have a some what dangerous job and i wanted to be right there on the front lines with all the other EMT's that got to go help... no mater what i tried to say i felt helpless there was no way i was going to be able to calm her fears and this totally frustrated me.... anyway we met the next day and talked about it and worked it out but it was a really tense couple days. 

on another note we are going to go watch SAW IV tonight i am so excited... im sure it will not disappoint

ok  so here goes my first entry... this could get weird... 
currently i am sitting across from my girlfriend and looking into her beautiful eyes, her soulful eyes, feeling a type of pull to a person i just havent felt in years... it is an awesome feeling it is engulfing and nearly indescribable... i have a peace and grounded aura where im around her... although i feel her hesitation for somethings i am grateful for the fact that she has pushed her boundaries so far to spend time with me and to do enjoyable things.... this kind of sacrifice is the greatest kind in my mind... i don't think she even can fathom the appreciation that i have and how much it means to me.... when i have feelings of doubt or insecurity i think of these things and i'm reassured
